title: Metro State Cycling Roadrunner Time Trial
1st Annual Rams Road Rivalry
description:
1st Annual Road Race will feature everything a cyclist of all levels loves and hates about Colorado looping through the foothills west of fort collins, co.
1st annual Team Time Trial will be an event for Collegiate racers only on the same course as the road race.
22nd Annual Criterium will be held as traditionally around the Colorado State university campus and open to all levels.
course: Road Race and Team Time Trial course will be an approximate 9 mile loop around Masonville, CO in the area west of Fort Collins, south of the horsetooth resevoir. This loop will start on north glade road, turn on W cr-24th, then loop back to the start point on 56.
registration: Registration will be available online through active.com, or at the start / finish both days with no late fee charged.

title: CC Campu Crit and Cheyenne Canyon Hill Climb
USAFA Road Race
flyer_url: Falcon Cycling Collegiate Road Race Flyer 2007.doc
description: This is a collegiate road race event hosted by the United States Air Force Academy Cycling Team.
course: The course will be a 12.7 mile per lap, clockwise loop around the U.S. Air Force Academy. Staging and parking will be at the athletic fields.
notes: Due to the varying security measures at the Air Force Academy some or all of the sections of the race course may be closed to the public. As a result, only racers with visible numbers will be allowed through security checkpoints.
directions: From I-25, take the North Gate exit (exit 156B). Head west towards the Academy, go through the North Gate entrance and continue on this road until you descend from the overlook. Take the first left towards the athletic fields and follow the signs to appropriate parking. Signs will be posted along Academy roads from North Gate to guide racers.
